OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1778691955
OL,3,C'I've been spat at and abused', says
OL,4,Ccouncil leader stepping down
OL,6,FShe said West Lancashire councillors
OL,7,Fare generally respectful to each
OL,8,Fother, despite political differences.
OL,9,FBut wider public debates and social
OL,10,Fmedia are increasingly hostile.
OL,12,FShe said: "We're the first council to
OL,13,Fbe building new homes since the 1970s.
OL,14,FYet we're being criticised for
OL,15,Feverything and Labour councillors have
OL,16,Flost their seats in the elections. As
OL,17,Ffar as I'm concerned, Reform is not
OL,18,Fthe party of the people. Now, people
OL,19,Fwill see what Reform is really about."
OL,26,@tD@KOU{D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
